HEADWORD: Stalked
<hw>Stalked</hw> <pr>(st⟦add⟧kt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a stalk
or stem; borne upon a stem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stalked barnacle</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
goose barnacle, or anatifer; -- called also <altname>stalk
barnacle</altname>.</cd> -- <col><b>Stalked crinoid</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any crinoid having a jointed stem.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stalker</ent>⟦br⟧
